Add OmniScripts to Adobe Experience Manager using OmniOut. OmniScripts hosted in AEM require a Salesforce connection to send data between servers.

Before You Begin

Learn about OmniOut. See OmniOut.

Test your OmniScripts in OmniOut's development mode. See Run OmniOut in Development Mode.

Create a Salesforce connection in AEM. See Integrate Salesforce Cloud Services into Adobe Experience Manager.
Set resource paths in OmniOut to load Lightning and Newport styles into your app. See Set the OmniOut Resource Path.
Deploy OmniOut to AEM. See Deploy OmniOut to Adobe Experience Manager.
Add the OmniOut component to an AEM page. See Add the Vlocity LWC OmniOut Component to Adobe Experience Manager.

Integrate Salesforce Cloud Services into Adobe Experience Manager
Create a Salesforce connection in AEM. The connection setup isnâ€™t part of the Vlocity package.
Set the OmniOut Resource Path
Load your custom styling resources into your Adobe Experience Manager application by setting the correct resource paths.
Deploy OmniOut to Adobe Experience Manager
Add your AEM credentials to OmniOut and deploy it to your AEM server.

Add the Vlocity LWC OmniOut Component to Adobe Experience Manager
Launch OmniScripts from an AEM page by adding the Vlocity LWC OmniOut Component. The Vlocity LWC OmniOut component hosts the OmniScript and uses the Salesforce Cloud Services configuration to make calls to Salesforce.
